'''Nicolás Iván González''' ({{IPA|es|nikoˈlas iˈβaŋ ɡonˈsales}}; born 6 April 1998) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]], on loan from [[Serie A]] club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]], and the [[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]].

==Club career==
===Argentinos Juniors===
After over ten years in the club's youth system,<ref name="Argentinos profile">{{Cite news|title=Nicolás González profile|url=http://www.argentinosjuniors.com.ar/futbol/profesional/plantel/perfil/2522_nicolasgonzalez|website=Argentinos Juniors|date=2 November 2017|language=es|archive-date=9 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171109052833/http://www.argentinosjuniors.com.ar/futbol/profesional/plantel/perfil/2522_nicolasgonzalez |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="Argentinos interview">{{Cite news|title=Conociendo a Nicolás González|url=http://www.argentinosjuniors.com.ar/futbol/amateur/juvenil/noticias/20160525_5826|website=Argentinos Juniors|access-date=2 November 2017|language=es|archive-date=7 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107030208/http://www.argentinosjuniors.com.ar/futbol/amateur/juvenil/noticias/20160525_5826 |url-status=dead }}</ref> González made his professional debut for [[Argentinos Juniors]] in a [[2015–16 Copa Argentina]] defeat to [[Deportivo Laferrere]] of [[Primera C Metropolitana]] in July 2016.<ref name="Soccerway profile">{{Cite news|date=2 November 2017|title=Nicolás González profile|work=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/nicolas-gonzalez/450709/|access-date=2 November 2017}}</ref> He made his [[Primera B Nacional]] debut on 28 August against [[San Martín de Tucumán|San Martín]] prior to scoring the first of his four goals in [[2016–17 Primera B Nacional|2016–17]] on 23 April 2017, getting the winner against [[Club Atlético Paraná|Atlético Paraná]].<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> In total, González made twenty appearances in 2016–17, a season which ended with Argentinos winning promotion to the [[Argentine Primera División]].<ref name="Soccerway profile" /><ref name="BDFA profile">{{Cite news|title=Nicolás González profile|url=http://www.bdfa.com.ar/jugadores-NICOLAS-GONZALEZ-108541.html|website=Argentine Primera División|date=2 November 2017|language=es}}</ref><ref name="Argentinos promotion">{{Cite news|title=¡Gritalo Bicho!: González y el gol del ascenso|url=http://www.tycsports.com/futbol/gritalo-bicho-gonzalez-y-el-gol-del-ascenso|website=[[TyC Sports]]|date=8 July 2017|access-date=2 November 2017|language=es}}</ref> He scored on his first top-flight start, scoring the opening goal in a defeat to [[Club Atlético Belgrano|Belgrano]].<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>

===VfB Stuttgart===
On 10 July 2018, González signed a five-year contract with [[VfB Stuttgart]].<ref name="VfB Stuttgart 1">{{Cite news|title=VfB sign Nicolás Gonzalez|url=http://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2018/vfb-stuttgart-verpflichtet-nicolas-gonzalez-/|website=VfB Stuttgart|date=10 July 2018|access-date=10 July 2018}}</ref> He scored twice on his unofficial debut for the club, netting in a friendly victory over [[FV Illertissen]] on 18 July.<ref name="VfB Stuttgart 2">{{Cite news|title=FV Illertissen vs. VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/friendly-match/2018/fv-illertissen-vfb-stuttgart-/|date=18 July 2018|access-date=27 July 2018}}</ref> His first competitive goal arrived during a home loss to [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on 22 December.<ref name="Soccerway profile" /> They were relegated at the end of [[2018–19 VfB Stuttgart season|2018–19]], with González subsequently scoring the winner on his [[2. Bundesliga]] bow against [[FC St. Pauli]] on 17 August 2019.<ref name="STN1">{{Cite news|title=Überglücklicher Nicolas Gonzalez|url=https://www.stuttgarter-nachrichten.de/inhalt.siegtorschuetze-des-vfb-stuttgart-uebergluecklicher-nicolas-gonzalez.438152be-b869-4fa6-a422-daca1326ed55.html|website=Stuttgarter Nachrichten|date=17 August 2019}}</ref> He scored consecutive braces in June 2020 against [[SV Sandhausen|Sandhausen]] and [[1. FC Nürnberg|Nürnberg]], the latter of which was his 100th league appearance for Stuttgart.<ref name="Soccerway profile" /><ref name="MA1">{{Cite news|title=Nicolas Gonzalez scores twice for Stuttgart as Bundesliga promotion nears|url=https://mundoalbiceleste.com/2020/06/22/nicolas-gonzalez-scores-twice-for-stuttgart-as-bundesliga-promotion-nears/|website=Mundo Albiceleste|date=22 June 2020|access-date=26 June 2020}}</ref>

On 25 November 2020, González extended his contract with VfB Stuttgart until June 2024.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Nicolas Gonzalez signs contract extension|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2020/vertragsverlaengerung-nicolas-gonzalez/|website=VfB Stuttgart|date=25 November 2020}}</ref>

===Fiorentina===
On 23 June 2021, González signed a five-year contract with [[Serie A]] club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Welcome, Nicolás González!|url=http://www.acffiorentina.com/en/news/all/news-men-first-team/2021-06-23/welcome-nicolas-gonzalez|website=ACF Fiorentina|date=23 June 2021|access-date=23 June 2021|archive-date=29 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629014331/https://www.acffiorentina.com/en/news/all/news-men-first-team/2021-06-23/welcome-nicolas-gonzalez|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 13 August, González made his debut for Fiorentina in a 4–0 win against [[Serie B]] side [[Cosenza Calcio|Cosenza]] in the first round of [[Coppa Italia]] scoring the second goal in the 37th minute.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Buona la prima per Italiano: poker della Fiorentina al Cosenza. Sugli scudi Vlahovic e Nico Gonzalez|url=https://www.fiorentinanews.com/buona-la-prima-per-italiano-poker-della-fiorentina-al-cosenza-sugli-scudi-vlahovic-e-nico-gonzalez/|website=Fiorentina News|date=13 August 2021|language=it}}</ref> On 18 May 2023, González scored a brace in Fiorentina's second leg [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] semi-final victory against [[FC Basel|Basel]], sending his side to the [[2023 UEFA Europa Conference League final|final]] against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].{{Citation needed|date=April 2024}}

=== Juventus ===
On 25 August 2024, González joined [[Serie A]] club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] on a season-long loan with an obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nico Gonzalez is Bianconero! |url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/nico-gonzalez-is-bianconero |publisher=Juventus FC |access-date=25 August 2024 |date=25 August 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Gonzalez ceduto alla Juventus |url=https://www.acffiorentina.com/it/news/tutte/prima-squadra-maschile/2024-08-25/gonzalez-ceduto-alla-juventus |publisher=ACF Fiorentina |access-date=25 August 2024 |language=Italian |date=25 August 2024 }}</ref> Juventus reported the transfer fees as €8 million for the 2024–25 season loan (with up to €0.4 million in additional costs), followed by the permanent transfer for €25 million, with an additional performance-based fees up to €5 million. The obligation to buy is conditional, but the conditions are highly likely to be triggered, thus Juventus accounted for the move as a permanent transfer.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Juventus FC|url=https://www.juventus.com/images/image/private/fl_attachment/dev/lojkbuhysaztywvraj2l.pdf|title=AGREEMENT WITH FIORENTINA FOR THE ACQUISITION OF THE PLAYER DI GONZALEZ|date=25 August 2024}}</ref>

A month later, on 17 September, he scored his first goal on his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut in a 3–1 win over [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Coates |first=Charlotte |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cvgwe4ke8d4t |title=Juventus 3–1 PSV |publisher=BBC Sport |date=17 September 2024 }}</ref> In summer 2025, Juventus signed González permanently for a reported transfer fee of €28.1 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://oldjuve.com/juventus-open-to-offers-for-winger-they-only-just-bought |title=Juventus open to offers for winger they only just bought |publisher=oldjuve.com |date=17 July 2025 }}</ref>

==== Loan to Atlético Madrid ====
On 1 September 2025, González joined [[La Liga]] club [[Atlético Madrid]] on an initial loan deal worth €1 million with an obligation to buy for €35 million depending on the number of games he  plays for Atlético.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-01 |title=Club Atlético de Madrid - ¡Bienvenido, Nico Gonzalez! |url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/bienvenido-nico-gonzalez |access-date=2025-09-01 |website=Club Atlético de Madrid |language=es-ES}}</ref> He made his debut on 13 September in a league match against Villarreal CF, scoring a goal to help seal a 2–0 victory in his first appearance for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-13 |title=Nicolás González scores on debut for Atlético Madrid in 2-0 win vs. Villarreal {{!}} Mundo Albiceleste |url=https://mundoalbiceleste.com/2025/09/13/nicolas-gonzalez-scores-on-debut-for-atletico-madrid-in-2-0-win-vs-villarreal/ |access-date=2025-09-15 |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
In July 2019, González received a call-up from the [[Argentina national under-23 football team|Argentina Olympic Team]] for said year's [[Football at the 2019 Pan American Games – Men's tournament|Pan American Games]] in Peru.<ref name="AFA1">{{Cite news|title=Lista de convocados de la Selección Sub 23 para los Juegos Panamericanos|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/lista-de-convocados-de-la-seleccion-sub-23-para-los-juegos-panamericanos|date=17 July 2019|access-date=29 July 2019|language=es}}</ref> After receiving a red card on his debut against [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador]],<ref>{{Cite news|title=Nico González y su debut: "Lo disfruté al máximo"|trans-title=Nico González and his debut: "I enjoyed it to the fullest"|url=https://argentina.as.com/argentina/2019/10/13/futbol/1570992768_891716.html|website=[[Diario AS]]|date=13 October 2019|language=es}}</ref> he played again in the semi-final and the gold medal match when Argentina won the tournament.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/> Months later, González was selected by [[Lionel Scaloni]]'s [[Argentina national football team|senior team]] for the first time ahead of October friendly matches against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]].<ref name="AFA2">{{Cite news|title=Lista de convocados de la Selección Mayor y Sub 23 para la doble fecha FIFA de octubre|url=https://www.afa.com.ar/es/posts/lista-de-convocados-de-la-seleccion-mayor-y-sub-23-para-la-doble-fecha-fifa-de-octubre|website=Argentine Football Association|date=27 September 2019|access-date=13 October 2019|language=es}}</ref><ref name="CLA1">{{Cite news|title=Quién es Nicolás González, el juvenil que juega en la B de Alemania y fue titular en la Selección |work=Clarín |url=https://www.clarin.com/deportes/nicolas-gonzalez-argentina-ecuador_0_s0bLfOQD.html|date=12 October 2019|access-date=13 October 2019|language=es}}</ref> He did not feature in the matchday squad against Germany, but appeared for his international bow during a 6–1 victory over Ecuador at the [[Estadio Manuel Martínez Valero]] in [[Elche]] on 13 October.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>

González scored his first goal for Argentina on 12 November 2020 in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup]] qualifier against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] that ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref name="Soccerway profile"/>{{Better source needed|reason=Source does not clarify if it is his first goal|date=April 2024}} He netted again days later against the same opponent.{{Citation needed|date=April 2024}}

González was a member of the [[2021 Copa América]] winning side, making five appearances in the tournament, four as a starter and one as substitute in the [[2021 Copa América Final|final]] against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]. He was also called up to Argentina's [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] squad, but was forced to withdraw with a muscular injury three days before the start of the tournament, being replaced by [[Ángel Correa]].<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=Argentina|number=1593315253227487233|title=#SelecciónMayor Tras el entrenamiento de hoy, el futbolista Nicolás González sufrió una lesión muscular y quedará desafectado de la nómina mundialista. En su reemplazo, el CT de @Argentina, convoca a Ángel Correa.|date=17 November 2022}}</ref>{{Better source needed|date=April 2024}}

In June 2024, González was included in Lionel Scaloni's final 26-man Argentina squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 June 2024 |title=Lionel Scaloni dio a conocer la lista de la Selección argentina para la Copa América 2024 |url=https://tn.com.ar/deportes/futbol/2024/06/15/lionel-scaloni-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-la-seleccion-argentina-para-la-copa-america-2024/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwqf20BhBwEiwAt7dtdeK13_I24H4iqEBua7UtmDLn6_x-FfDm-gzEseLS8vJCnOlmjC3PlBoCHEwQAvD_BwE |access-date=23 July 2024 |work=Todo Noticias}}</ref> During the final against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]], González had to replace [[Lionel Messi]] after he suffered an ankle injury in the second half. 18 minutes after he entered the pitch he scored a goal, but it was ruled off.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Cristofanelli |first=Federico |date=15 July 2024 |title=El boletín de calificaciones de Argentina en la final ante Colombia: los puntos superlativos que maquillaron la baja de Messi y Lautaro Martínez héroe |url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes/2024/07/15/el-boletin-de-calificaciones-de-argentina-en-la-final-ante-colombia-los-puntos-superlativos-que-maquillaron-la-baja-de-messi-y-lautaro-martinez-heroe/ |access-date=23 July 2024 |website=Infobae}}</ref>

